1. What is the terminal?

The terminal is used as a tool to link to a computer with text-based commands.
macOS has a native app called Terminal.

2. What is the major difference between Git and GitHub?

Git is used to help developers keep track of changes while working on different parts of the same project globally. 

GitHub is a web app that can connect with Git. 

Users can host, organize, explore, and collaborate on code with teams(project management) and the universal developer community by linking both applications.

3.  What are the steps to fork a GitHub repository?

 click "Fork" (top-right corner of the page)
 Under "Owner," select the dropdown menu and click an owner for the forked repository
 type a new name in the "Repository name" field (optional)
 type a description in the "Description" field (optional)
 click "Create fork"